Never Gonna Give It Up!

00:02:14.510 --> 00:02:15.880
It's gonna take six months to heal,

00:02:15.880 --> 00:02:17.500
and I'm not running
until next spring?

00:02:17.500 --> 00:02:18.900
What do I care?

00:02:18.900 --> 00:02:22.330
You seriously think that's gonna 
get me to give up on the Kikkashou?

00:02:22.330 --> 00:02:23.740
You aren't, are you?

00:02:23.740 --> 00:02:26.180
I'm gonna enter! And I'm gonna win!

00:02:29.330 --> 00:02:32.440
All right, then... guess I better
 come up with a plan.

00:02:33.580 --> 00:02:36.630
I'm counting on you! I have to do this to 
become an undefeated Triple Crown winner.

00:02:36.630 --> 00:02:37.650
I know, I know...

00:02:37.870 --> 00:02:40.710
But the first step is to cooperate, 
and get admitted to the hospital.

00:02:41.300 --> 00:02:43.870
But I hate hospitals...

00:02:43.870 --> 00:02:45.870
TOKAI TEIO DIAGNOSED WITH FRACTURED LEG

00:02:45.870 --> 00:02:47.870
WITH SIX-MONTH RECOVERY EXPECTED,
 IS HER ENTRY IN THE KIKKASHOU IN DANGER?

00:02:46.690 --> 00:02:47.870
She's in the hospital?!

00:02:47.870 --> 00:02:51.370
No way! But she was in perfect shape 
during the race and the concert!

00:02:55.880 --> 00:02:57.630
Tokai Teio's <font color="#fcfa48">Leg Fracture</font>

00:02:57.840 --> 00:03:01.080
Tokai Teio would've totally won the Kikkashou
if she was able to run in it.

00:03:01.080 --> 00:03:03.160
But there's no way she makes it in time now.

00:03:03.160 --> 00:03:04.310
That's the thing!

