00:03:12.670 --> 00:03:14.860
The Kikkashou's in November.

00:03:16.520 --> 00:03:17.610
All right!

00:03:17.980 --> 00:03:19.610
I'm back!

00:03:19.610 --> 00:03:21.740
T-Teio?!

00:03:22.310 --> 00:03:24.480
You're already out of the hospital?

00:03:24.480 --> 00:03:25.870
Yeah!

00:03:25.870 --> 00:03:27.380
Well, you're acting like you're fine!

00:03:27.380 --> 00:03:28.630
There goes our peace and quiet.

00:03:28.630 --> 00:03:31.080
Oh, please, you were <i>so</i> worried about her!

00:03:31.080 --> 00:03:32.830
Teio, I've got it right here.

00:03:32.830 --> 00:03:36.540
Perfect Plan
for Tokai Teio's
 Return to Racing
 at the Kikkashou

00:03:33.090 --> 00:03:36.540
The perfect plan for Tokai Teio's 
return to racing at the Kikkashou!

00:03:36.540 --> 00:03:37.730
Look at all that!

00:03:37.730 --> 00:03:39.040
Pretty amazing, right?

00:03:39.540 --> 00:03:41.010
What's wrong, guys?

00:03:41.010 --> 00:03:43.400
Trainer-san, are you being serious?

00:03:43.400 --> 00:03:44.800
I sure am.

00:03:45.060 --> 00:03:48.120
If Teio hasn't given up yet, 
I'll do everything I can to support her.

00:03:48.120 --> 00:03:49.810
That's what I've decided.

00:03:49.810 --> 00:03:51.270
And I'm not giving up!

00:03:51.270 --> 00:03:53.100
I'm gonna make my comeback at the Kikkashou!

00:03:54.520 --> 00:03:56.510
Make me one promise, though.

00:03:56.510 --> 00:03:57.400
What's that?

00:03:57.400 --> 00:03:58.900
We'll hang in there until the last minute.

00:03:58.900 --> 00:04:02.740
But if the doctor says it's a no-go,
 then you have to give it up.

00:04:02.740 --> 00:04:04.550
Okay! I know!

00:04:04.550 --> 00:04:06.700
You scared me! What?!

00:04:06.700 --> 00:04:08.920
I'm just so touched right now!

00:04:08.920 --> 00:04:11.750
Teio! I'll help you any way I can!

00:04:11.750 --> 00:04:13.370
Coming from you, that's kind of scary.

00:04:13.370 --> 00:04:16.260
I want your dream to 
come true, too, Teio-san!

00:04:16.260 --> 00:04:18.880
I'm gonna make it happen. I'll be 
an undefeated Triple Crown winner!

00:04:18.880 --> 00:04:21.710
It doesn't seem like there's any 
room for argument, here.

00:04:21.710 --> 00:04:23.590
True enough. And if you give up—

00:04:23.590 --> 00:04:24.880
Hang in there, Teio!

00:04:25.090 --> 00:04:25.990
You know I will!

00:04:25.990 --> 00:04:28.100
All right, let's get started!

00:04:28.550 --> 00:04:31.180
The first step on your path to the Kikkashou!

00:04:41.770 --> 00:04:44.240
It looks like Teio-san's out of the hospital.

00:04:44.240 --> 00:04:48.030
Yes. She came to see me 
as soon as she got out.

00:04:48.350 --> 00:04:49.940
I'm back, Prez!

00:04:49.940 --> 00:04:51.670
You got out of the hospital quickly.

00:04:51.670 --> 00:04:52.660
I know, right?

00:04:52.660 --> 00:04:56.040
Just watch, Prez! I'll be 
running again in no time!

00:04:56.890 --> 00:04:58.790
That's really something.

00:04:58.790 --> 00:05:01.830
It's going to be a battle 
with herself from now on.

00:05:01.830 --> 00:05:03.530
Just like what you went through.

00:05:03.530 --> 00:05:04.400
Right.

00:05:04.400 --> 00:05:05.240
Begin!

00:05:12.270 --> 00:05:14.520
What part of your rehabilitation is this?

00:05:16.370 --> 00:05:18.440
It's called image training.

00:05:18.440 --> 00:05:20.480
You're gonna imagine what it's 
like once you're running again.

00:05:20.480 --> 00:05:25.360
Watch the others run, and always be 
thinking about what you would do!

00:05:26.570 --> 00:05:28.110
If it was me at this speed...

00:05:28.410 --> 00:05:31.240
Once I was in a good position,
I'd hang onto it.

00:05:31.650 --> 00:05:34.750
Spe-chan and Gold Ship are both 
great at closing the distance.

00:05:34.750 --> 00:05:39.140
But with that pressure on me, I'd keep 
my back to them all the way through.

00:05:39.500 --> 00:05:43.790
In that case, be sure to get a 
good look at how I run, too.

00:05:44.210 --> 00:05:47.170
Although I'm not sure you'll be able 
to keep up, even in your imagination.

00:05:47.170 --> 00:05:50.340
Trainer-san! I'd like to join in next.

00:05:50.340 --> 00:05:53.580
Teio! These used to be mine,
but you can have them.

00:05:55.950 --> 00:05:56.950
Heavy!

00:05:56.950 --> 00:05:58.520
What are these?

00:05:59.230 --> 00:06:00.480
Weights?

00:06:00.480 --> 00:06:02.990
How heavy are the dumbbells you lift, Teio?

00:06:02.990 --> 00:06:04.550
Vodka! That isn't fair, getting ahead of me!

00:06:04.550 --> 00:06:05.870
What does it matter?

00:06:05.870 --> 00:06:07.410
Teio, use this!

00:06:08.670 --> 00:06:11.020
It's important to work on your 
mental health at times like this!

00:06:11.020 --> 00:06:12.020
Thanks!

00:06:12.020 --> 00:06:13.700
Teio!

00:06:14.120 --> 00:06:16.790
I want you to use this. My S.S. <i>Golshi</i>.

00:06:16.790 --> 00:06:18.480
How do you ride it?

00:06:18.480 --> 00:06:19.600
You just gotta...

00:06:19.600 --> 00:06:21.030
H-huh?

00:06:21.030 --> 00:06:22.460
It's stuck.

00:06:22.460 --> 00:06:23.750
Teio-san...

00:06:22.460 --> 00:06:24.360
Maybe it's in a bad mood.

00:06:24.360 --> 00:06:26.700
Can I come by your room tonight?

00:06:24.720 --> 00:06:27.880
Come on, work with me here!

00:06:28.660 --> 00:06:30.870
Tips for rehabilitation?

00:06:30.870 --> 00:06:34.390
Right, I thought you'd be the 
best person to ask, Suzuka-san.

00:06:34.680 --> 00:06:38.390
I'm sorry, Suzuka. I told 
her not to bother, but...

00:06:38.390 --> 00:06:41.270
I'm relieved. You seem to be doing 
better than I worried you might.

00:06:41.270 --> 00:06:44.210
Yeah, same here. Have you lost weight?

00:06:44.210 --> 00:06:45.100
I think so.

00:06:45.100 --> 00:06:48.190
It took me a while to get 
used to the food over here.

00:06:48.190 --> 00:06:48.900
Suzuka-san,

00:06:48.900 --> 00:06:50.530
do you want me to send more carrots?!

00:06:50.530 --> 00:06:52.660
I've got plenty, thank you.

00:06:52.660 --> 00:06:54.950
Teio, congratulations on the Derby.

00:06:55.660 --> 00:06:56.550
Thanks.

00:06:56.550 --> 00:06:58.030
You're going to try for the Kikkashou?

00:06:58.030 --> 00:06:58.600
Yeah.

00:06:58.600 --> 00:07:00.860
That's going to make for 
a rough rehab period.

00:07:00.860 --> 00:07:02.140
Are you prepared?

00:07:03.050 --> 00:07:03.920
Yeah!

00:07:03.920 --> 00:07:07.320
The most important thing is 
to not push yourself too hard.

00:07:07.320 --> 00:07:11.310
If you rush it, you could 
end up injuring yourself again.

00:07:11.310 --> 00:07:14.180
Our Trainer said the same thing.

00:07:14.180 --> 00:07:16.650
But there's so little time...

00:07:16.650 --> 00:07:18.770
I know. And I understand how you feel.

00:07:18.770 --> 00:07:21.940
But getting plenty of rest is 
an important part of rehab.

00:07:21.940 --> 00:07:25.110
And there are things you can 
do while you're resting, too.

00:07:30.890 --> 00:07:31.970
Teio...

00:07:31.970 --> 00:07:33.200
What the hell is she doing?

00:07:33.410 --> 00:07:34.410
Research.

00:07:34.410 --> 00:07:35.710
Research?!

00:07:35.710 --> 00:07:37.620
Suzuka-san gave her some advice yesterday.

00:07:35.710 --> 00:07:37.620
Winning Data for Every Race
<font color="#e9f0ed"> The Racing Textbook
</font><font color="#555756"> Racing Theory for the Committed 
</font><font color="#d3cee9"> Everything There Is To Learn About Turf</font>

00:07:40.130 --> 00:07:42.650
All right, I've got some stuff to teach her!

00:07:42.650 --> 00:07:44.250
It's a bad idea to try make your move right

00:07:44.250 --> 00:07:46.840
before the third corner of
the outer track in Kyoto!

00:07:46.840 --> 00:07:49.020
Aw, would you keep it down?

00:07:46.840 --> 00:07:49.840
Got that? No matter what!

00:07:49.840 --> 00:07:52.030
That last race was a close one.

00:07:52.030 --> 00:07:52.840
Hey...

00:07:54.080 --> 00:07:57.350
What would you say if I told you I was 
thinking about entering the Kikkashou?

00:07:57.350 --> 00:07:59.010
Kikkashou?! G-1?!

00:07:59.010 --> 00:08:00.820
It probably wouldn't work... right?

00:08:00.820 --> 00:08:01.830
I wanna enter, too!

00:08:01.830 --> 00:08:03.440
Turbo-san, you'd need to win more first.

00:08:03.440 --> 00:08:04.240
Then I will!

00:08:04.240 --> 00:08:05.560
I'll totally win the next race!

00:08:05.560 --> 00:08:09.350
If I can keep coming in first place 
with the next few races, can I manage?

00:08:09.350 --> 00:08:10.980
Give me just a second.

00:08:11.960 --> 00:08:14.600
You're feeling fired up, 
huh, Nature? How come?

00:08:15.430 --> 00:08:17.200
Teio might still be running in it.

00:08:17.200 --> 00:08:18.830
Tokai Teio?

00:08:18.830 --> 00:08:19.940
But she's...

00:08:19.940 --> 00:08:21.500
She hasn't given up.

00:08:23.150 --> 00:08:27.340
So... I might not be up for it, but...

00:08:29.900 --> 00:08:32.590
If I win this, this, and the Kokura Kinen...

00:08:32.590 --> 00:08:33.940
Will I be able to enter?

00:08:33.940 --> 00:08:35.340
Uh, yes.

00:08:35.340 --> 00:08:37.510
Let's get cracking on some training, then!

00:08:37.510 --> 00:08:39.870
Okay, I'm gonna give this a try!

00:08:37.510 --> 00:08:41.520
Aim for a G1 Win!

00:08:42.350 --> 00:08:43.980
You can do it, Teio!

00:08:43.030 --> 00:08:44.370
I watch all your races!

00:08:58.520 --> 00:08:59.530
What?

00:08:59.740 --> 00:09:01.790
What? What?!

00:09:01.790 --> 00:09:04.670
What, what, what?! What the heck?

00:09:04.670 --> 00:09:05.680
What is all this?!

00:09:05.680 --> 00:09:08.130
You want to be ready in time 
for the Kikkashou, right?

00:09:08.490 --> 00:09:11.660
This is the Mejiro family physical therapist.

00:09:11.660 --> 00:09:13.050
I'm the physical therapist.

00:09:13.050 --> 00:09:14.250
Acupuncturist.

00:09:14.250 --> 00:09:15.720
I'm the acupuncturist.

00:09:15.720 --> 00:09:16.470
Chef.

00:09:16.470 --> 00:09:17.430
I'm the chef.

00:09:17.460 --> 00:09:18.460
Patissier.

00:09:18.460 --> 00:09:19.800
I'm the patissier.

00:09:19.800 --> 00:09:21.940
You are welcome to spend the weekend

00:09:21.940 --> 00:09:25.740
relaxing here at the estate 
in luxury, Teio-sama.

00:09:25.740 --> 00:09:29.520
O-Okay... McQueen, what's going on?

00:09:29.520 --> 00:09:32.690
I thought it'd be a good idea 
to use every resource available.

00:09:32.690 --> 00:09:34.670
The family physician is also available.

00:09:34.670 --> 00:09:36.090
That's me.

00:09:41.200 --> 00:09:43.160
Why do you have that needle?!

00:09:43.160 --> 00:09:44.950
Because I am the young lady's family doctor.

00:09:44.950 --> 00:09:46.440
That doesn't explain anything!

00:09:46.440 --> 00:09:48.250
I'll be taking my leave, then.

00:09:48.250 --> 00:09:50.990
If there's anything you're 
unclear on, let me know.

00:09:50.990 --> 00:09:53.300
I just <i>said</i> I don't get what's going on!

00:09:54.990 --> 00:09:59.010
McQueen... don't abandon me... please...

00:09:59.010 --> 00:10:03.010
Umamusume

00:09:59.010 --> 00:10:03.010
{\an2}Pretty Derby

00:10:05.230 --> 00:10:06.770
The cast is off!

00:10:06.770 --> 00:10:08.630
I won't have to wear the 
brace for long, either.

00:10:09.900 --> 00:10:12.110
This is where it gets serious. Got it?

00:10:13.520 --> 00:10:16.780
Sweets! Sweets! Sweets!

00:10:22.990 --> 00:10:24.660
You wanna run, Teio?

00:10:24.660 --> 00:10:26.540
Of course I do!

00:10:26.540 --> 00:10:28.150
Well, hold back!

00:10:28.150 --> 00:10:31.070
Take that desire to run 
and convert it to energy!

00:10:31.070 --> 00:10:35.410
You're gonna need to teach your 
leg again that it's a runner's leg!

00:10:35.410 --> 00:10:36.800
Yeah!

00:10:40.740 --> 00:10:42.220
Stay focused, Spe.

00:10:42.630 --> 00:10:44.690
I just keep wondering how she's doing.

00:10:44.690 --> 00:10:49.420
The only thing we can really do for 
Teio is to show her our backs as we run.

00:10:49.420 --> 00:10:50.100
Right!

00:10:50.100 --> 00:10:52.190
Nicely put, McQueen!

00:10:52.190 --> 00:10:53.700
And with that being the case...

00:10:53.700 --> 00:10:54.860
Hey, no fair!

00:10:54.860 --> 00:10:56.160
I'm going, too!

00:10:56.160 --> 00:10:57.170
You wanna take me on?!

00:10:57.170 --> 00:10:58.300
I won't be outdone!

00:10:58.300 --> 00:11:01.220
Argh, I wanna run, too!

00:11:01.220 --> 00:11:04.170
That's the spirit! Don't forget that feeling!

00:11:36.860 --> 00:11:38.110
May I sit here?

00:11:39.680 --> 00:11:40.640
Sure!

00:11:40.640 --> 00:11:41.870
How are you doing?

00:11:41.870 --> 00:11:44.290
Right on schedule! What else did you expect?

00:11:44.290 --> 00:11:46.990
You really are something, Teio.

00:11:46.990 --> 00:11:49.240
You seem to be doing well, too, Nature.
 You're on a three-win streak.

00:11:49.240 --> 00:11:50.490
I guess I am.

00:11:50.490 --> 00:11:51.910
Pardon me.

00:11:51.910 --> 00:11:53.360
Hey, you came.

00:11:53.820 --> 00:11:55.420
Nature, who's this?

00:11:55.420 --> 00:11:57.880
Canopus has another new member.

00:11:58.190 --> 00:11:59.770
I'm Ikuno Dictus.

00:11:58.210 --> 00:12:01.610
I
k
u
n
o
D
i
c
t
u
s

00:11:59.770 --> 00:12:01.180
It's a pleasure to meet you.

00:12:01.180 --> 00:12:02.780
N-Nice to meet you!

00:12:02.780 --> 00:12:06.680
Canopus is aiming to become 
the school's foremost team.

00:12:06.680 --> 00:12:07.740
We are?

00:12:07.740 --> 00:12:11.180
Were you not the one who suggested 
we aim high, Nature-san?

00:12:11.180 --> 00:12:12.770
I guess so!

00:12:12.770 --> 00:12:14.280
I think I remember saying that.

00:12:14.280 --> 00:12:15.400
It's all right.

00:12:15.400 --> 00:12:19.500
If we execute my plan, it's possible 
for us to achieve that goal.

00:12:19.500 --> 00:12:22.290
What we need in order to accomplish that 
is an overwhelming amount of experience.

00:12:22.290 --> 00:12:26.060
As well as the robust physicality 
and steely mentality

00:12:23.370 --> 00:12:26.060
I guess your team's got 
another interesting new girl.

00:12:26.060 --> 00:12:27.160
I guess.

00:12:26.060 --> 00:12:28.510
necessary to withstand such rigorous rotation.

00:12:27.160 --> 00:12:28.510
Anyway, Teio...

00:12:28.510 --> 00:12:31.670
I'm fully aware that it won't be a 
simple task to achieve these things.

00:12:29.070 --> 00:12:31.670
I'm going to be entering the trials.

00:12:31.670 --> 00:12:33.250
But I believe that a single tangible experience

00:12:31.670 --> 00:12:34.510
And if I win there, I'll 
be racing in the Kikkashou.

00:12:33.250 --> 00:12:34.800
is more valuable than 
100 theoretical situations.

00:12:34.800 --> 00:12:36.450
And no experience is more valuable than racing.

00:12:36.020 --> 00:12:37.160
I'll be waiting.

00:12:36.450 --> 00:12:37.600
It is all about racing.

00:12:37.160 --> 00:12:39.880
Because it's my dream to beat you.

00:12:37.600 --> 00:12:39.450
Which is to say that in 
training to race,

00:12:39.450 --> 00:12:41.070
races themselves are a 
part of your training.

00:12:41.070 --> 00:12:42.420
There is a school of thought that says

00:12:41.790 --> 00:12:42.630
Right!

00:12:42.420 --> 00:12:44.830
to train like you're in 
the actual competition.

00:12:44.830 --> 00:12:45.630
Thus, by all means...

